<paragraph id="F1053680FFD4F558FF715CBC6699FA69" blockId="11.[151,1437,1233,1476]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">
Type data: 
<bibRefCitation id="952B4B71FFD4F558FEF35CBF6599FAD9" author="Smith, F." box="[277,427,1269,1296]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" pagination="199 - 465" refId="ref19938" refString="Smith, F. (1854) Catalogue of Hymenopterous Insects in the Collection of the British Museum. Part 2. British Museum, London, 267 pp. [pp. 199 - 465]" type="book chapter" year="1854">Smith (1854)</bibRefCitation>
described this species based on an undetermined number of male specimens collected in an unknown locality in 
<collectingCountry id="89AD7610FFD4F558FE085D536604FAFA" box="[494,566,1305,1331]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. A specimen belonging to the type series is currently housed at 
<collectionCode id="97ABAE45FFD4F558FAE45D50615EFAFD" box="[1282,1388,1306,1332]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" name="Natural History Museum, London" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" type="Museum">NHMUK</collectionCode>
and is here designated the 
<typeStatus id="2E018822FFD4F558FE3B5D776675FA9E" box="[477,583,1341,1367]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The specimen has the following data label: Type H. 
<collectionCode id="97ABAE45FFD4F558FB725D746095FA91" box="[1172,1191,1342,1368]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">T</collectionCode>
. [red-rimmed circular label, printed]\ B.M. 
<collectionCode id="97ABAE45FFD4F558FE345D28662AFAB5" box="[466,536,1378,1404]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">TYPE</collectionCode>
<collectionCode id="97ABAE45FFD4F558FDC65D286657FAB5" box="[544,613,1378,1404]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">HYM</collectionCode>
. [printed] 17B.908 [handwritten]\ [light blue label] 
<collectingCountry id="89AD7610FFD4F558FB565D2B60C6FAB2" box="[1200,1268,1377,1403]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">Brazil</collectingCountry>
[handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName id="36BA4D03FFD4F558FF055DCC65F4FA56" authority="Sm" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1854" box="[227,454,1413,1440]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis id="C3CEEA92FFD4F558FF055DCC65ABFA56" box="[227,409,1413,1440]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">Centris modesta</emphasis>
Sm
</taxonomicName>
Type [handwritten].
</paragraph>
