</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F1053680FFD4F558FF715DBB655FF9B1" blockId="11.[151,1437,1521,1728]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">
Comments: Shortly after its description, 
<taxonomicName id="36BA4D03FFD4F558FD885DB866DDF9C2" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1854" box="[622,751,1521,1548]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis id="C3CEEA92FFD4F558FD885DB866B3F9C5" box="[622,641,1522,1548]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C3CEEA92FFD4F558FD745DBB66DDF9C2" box="[658,751,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was proposed as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="36BA4D03FFD4F558FB505DB864EEF9E6" authority="(Ducke, 1910)" baseAuthorityName="Ducke" baseAuthorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obsoleta">
<emphasis id="C3CEEA92FFD4F558FB505DB860FBF9C5" box="[1206,1225,1522,1548]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C3CEEA92FFD4F558FB3C5DBB610BF9C2" box="[1242,1337,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">obsoleta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="952B4B71FFD4F558FAAD5DBB64E1F9E6" author="Ducke, A." pageId="11" pageNumber="162" pagination="362 - 369" refId="ref18241" refString="Ducke, A. (1910) Zur Synonymie der neotropischen Apidae. (Hym.). Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 6, 362 - 369." type="journal article" year="1910">Ducke, 1910</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This synonymy remained unchanged until now that the 
<typeStatus id="2E018822FFD4F558FCB25E5F67F4F9E6" box="[852,966,1557,1583]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">lectotypes</typeStatus>
of both species were studied in detail. Although superficially similar, both species are valid, so the synonymy proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="952B4B71FFD4F558FBD65E7360F9F99A" author="Ducke, A." box="[1072,1227,1593,1619]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" pagination="362 - 369" refId="ref18241" refString="Ducke, A. (1910) Zur Synonymie der neotropischen Apidae. (Hym.). Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 6, 362 - 369." type="journal article" year="1910">Ducke (1910)</bibRefCitation>
must be no longer considered correct.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F1053680FFD4F558FF215ECB670FF976" blockId="11.[151,1437,1521,1728]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">
The 
<typeStatus id="2E018822FFD4F558FF1D5EC86519F955" box="[251,299,1666,1692]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">type</typeStatus>
locality cannot be further narrowed down than to 
<collectingCountry id="89AD7610FFD4F558FC8D5ECB6780F952" box="[875,946,1665,1691]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, although 
<bibRefCitation id="952B4B71FFD4F558FBCF5ECB60F2F952" author="Friese, H." box="[1065,1216,1665,1691]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" pagination="237 - 350" refId="ref18512" refString="Friese, H. (1901) Monographie der Bienengattung Centris (s. lat). Annalen des K. K. Naturhistorischen Hofmuseums, Wien, 15, 237 - 350." type="journal article" year="1901">Friese (1901)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that the specimen was collected in the northern locality of Santar√©m.
</paragraph>
